race.comment: HERE THE CROWD (7) went close at Pakenham first-up and she's won 2/3 second-up. Delivered at her only start this course/distance and gets in well with Houston's 2kg claim. Has more to give and is left the one to beat. YOOMEE WONDER (13) ran a decent number winning at Moe and Damian Lane is a positive jockey engagement. Has some weight relief and deserves consideration both ways. KYLE (4) peaks and is busting to win. There was only 1.4L in it at Cranbourne last time this grade/trip and he maps to get all the favours. DON'T RUSSIA (9) found more like her best beaten less than 2L at Sale over a shorter sprint. She jumped a short-priced favourite and will be fitter again. The 1200m is a worry with her, but she has weight relief and a soft barrier. Newitt will give her every chance to run it out.
